---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/astro/Section.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Code of Conduct | ZurichJS"
  description="ZurichJS Code of Conduct - Our community guidelines for creating an inclusive, respectful, and welcoming environment for all JavaScript developers in Zurich."
  keywords={['ZurichJS', 'JavaScript Zurich', 'community guidelines', 'code of conduct', 'inclusive community']}
>
  <Section variant="white" padding="lg">
    <div class="animate-fade-in-up max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Code of Conduct</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 mb-8">Effective guidelines for all ZurichJS events and community spaces.</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            ZurichJS is dedicated to providing a harassment-free, inclusive experience for everyone, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, religion, or technology choices. We do not tolerate harassment of community members in any form.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Expected Behavior</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Be respectful and considerate in your speech and actions.</li>
            <li>Practice empathy and kindness toward other community members.</li>
            <li>Be open to differing viewpoints and experiences.</li>
            <li>Give and gracefully accept constructive feedback.</li>
            <li>Focus on what is best for the community as a whole.</li>
            <li>Respect the boundaries and privacy of others.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Unacceptable Behavior</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            The following behaviors are considered unacceptable within our community:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination in any form.</li>
            <li>Verbal or written abuse, including offensive comments related to personal characteristics.</li>
            <li>Deliberate intimidation, stalking, or following.</li>
            <li>Unwelcome sexual attention or advances.</li>
            <li>Sustained disruption of talks, workshops, or other events.</li>
            <li>Publishing others' private information without explicit permission.</li>
            <li>Advocating for or encouraging any of the above behaviors.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Reporting</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, or have any other concerns, please report it as soon as possible. You can reach us directly at
            <a href="mailto:hello@zurichjs.com" class="text-yellow-600 hover:text-yellow-700 underline">hello@zurichjs.com</a>.
            All reports will be handled with discretion and confidentiality. You may also speak to any ZurichJS organizer at an event.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Enforcement</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Community organizers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing standards of acceptable behavior. In response to any incidents, organizers may take action they deem appropriate, including but not limited to: a warning, temporary ban, or permanent expulsion from the community and its events without refund. Organizers have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject contributions, comments, and other interactions that are not aligned with this Code of Conduct.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            If you have questions or concerns about this Code of Conduct, please contact us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@zurichjs.com" class="text-yellow-600 hover:text-yellow-700 underline">hello@zurichjs.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-8 border-gray-200" />

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-yellow-600 hover:text-yellow-700 font-medium">
        &larr; Back to Home
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</PageLayout>
